text: Miehikkälä is a municipality in Kymenlaakso, Finland. As of 28 February 2023, 1,784 people lived there, which makes it the smallest municipality in the region by population. Neighbouring municipalities are Hamina, Kouvola, Lappeenranta, Luumäki and Virolahti. Most people speak Finnish. == Other websites == * Municipality of Miehikkälä – Official website Category:Municipalities of Kymenlaakso
